  "body": "I cannot get the write path to write using `kubectl config set-credentials`  v1.1.2 or v1.1.4. I suspect this affects other versions and other arguments.\n#1\n\n`kubectl config set-credentials admin --client-certificate=.kube/ssl/admin.pem --client-key=.kube/ssl/admin.pem`\n\nresults in:\n\n```\n- name: admin\n  user:\n    client-certificate: ssl/admin.pem\n    client-key: ssl/admin.pem\n```\n#2\n\n`kubectl config set-credentials admin --client-certificate=~/.kube/ssl/admin.pem --client-key=~/.kube/ssl/admin.pem`\n\nresults in\n\n```\n- name: admin\n  user:\n    client-certificate: /Users/bloo/~/.kube/ssl/admin.pem\n    client-key: /Users/bloo/~/.kube/ssl/admin.pem\n```\n#3\n\n```\necho $HOME\n/Users/bloo\n```\n\nand \n\n`kubectl config set-credentials admin --client-certificate=${HOME}/.kube/ssl/admin.pem --client-key=${HOME}/.kube/ssl/admin.pem`\n\nresults in\n\n```\n- name: admin\n  user:\n    client-certificate: ssl/admin.pem\n    client-key: ssl/admin.pem\n```\n#4\n\n```\necho $HOME\n/Users/bloo\n```\n\nand \n\n`kubectl config set-credentials admin --client-certificate=$HOME/.kube/ssl/admin.pem --client-key=$HOME/.kube/ssl/admin.pem`\n\n```\n- name: admin\n  user:\n    client-certificate: ssl/admin.pem\n    client-key: ssl/admin.pem\n```\n#5\n\n`kubectl config set-credentials admin --client-certificate='.kube/ssl/admin.pem' --client-key='.kube/ssl/admin.pem'`\n\nresults in \n\n```\n- name: admin\n  user:\n    client-certificate: ssl/admin.pem\n    client-key: ssl/admin.pem\n```\n",
